Super Eagles captain at the recently ended Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) Cameroon 2021, Williams Troost-Ekong , believed Nigerians will see a ‘very hungry’ side for next month’s pivotal Qatar 2022 FIFA World Cup play-off against the Black Stars. Ghana will host the first leg of the two-legged encounters at the Cape Coast Stadium on 24th March with the reverse fixture holding on 29th Match at the Moshood Abiola Stadium in Abuja. “ Nigerians are going to see a very, very hungry team against Ghana in March, “ the 28-year-old Troost-Ekong told NationSport .“ A team that is ready to give everything in order to see our country at the next World Cup in Qatar.”   PDP governors urge Buhari to sign Electoral Act Amendment…     APC Convention: Sale of forms fails to begin     ASUU grounds varsities for four weeks   The Watford who star for the Super Eagles at the Russia 2018 World Cup, said the global football tournament is so important and crucial hence Nigeria cannot afford to miss out of the first World Cup to be hosted in the Middle East. “ I was at the last World Cup (Russia 2018) and I will say it’s the biggest highlight of my career and I will like to go there again and do better than we did last time. - Advertisement - “ I know what impact this would make ; and I know the boys will be fired up and we are going to be a very hungry team and give their best so that they can make Nigeria proud again after the disappointment of the AFCON. “ We would as a matter of fact be using that as a motivation in order to qualify for the World Cup ; and that is what I can say for now, “ added Troost-Ekong who was yesterday announced as the global ambassador for Game of Our Lives —a social action platform under the auspices of END Fund towards elimination of NTDs in Africa. (www.gameofourliv.es/thrivesafrica) SPONSORED